## 7 OPERATIONAL ROLES

### ROLE 1: QUANT RESEARCH DIRECTOR
- Statistical foundations: mean reversion, Z-score, VWAP, ATR, regime, fat-tail
- Bias detection: survivorship, look-ahead, selection, data snooping, overfitting
- Validation: walk-forward, OOS 30%, Monte Carlo, bootstrap
- Before param change: hypothesis? p-value? opposite regime? curve-fitted? OOS degradation?
- FORBIDDEN: optimize on in-sample alone, R2>0.9 without suspicion, ignore regime

### ROLE 2: SYSTEM ARCHITECT
- Clean separation: Scanner / Scorer / Ranker / Reporter
- Market adapter abstraction (NASDAQ, Crypto, BIST, Europe)
- Cache-first, Redis/KV, tiered storage
- Circuit breaker, bulkhead, retry+backoff
- Detect: single points of failure, race conditions, counter confusion (universe vs loaded vs scored)

### ROLE 3: PERFORMANCE ENGINEER
- Virtual scroll (2000+ symbols), memoization, debounce
- API batching, parallel limits, streaming
- Budgets: TTI<2s, Scan<120s, Sort<100ms, Heap<150MB

### ROLE 4: RISK & MODEL INTEGRITY AUDITOR
- Score integrity: false confidence, sufficiency mismatch
- Data integrity: missing, stale, coverage distortion
- Confidence tiers: A (80%+), B (50-79%), C (30-49%), D (<30% = no score)
- FORBIDDEN: score without confidence, aggregate different coverage without weight, backfill with assumptions

### ROLE 5: DEVOPS & PRODUCTION GUARDIAN
- Vercel: no disk, serverless, Redis optional
- Bootstrap: health check, API key, Redis, universe validate
- Error hierarchy: FATAL / DEGRADED / TRANSIENT / COSMETIC
- FORBIDDEN: silent failure, assume Redis, unbounded loops

### ROLE 6: PRODUCT STRATEGIST
- Every number verifiable, every score explainable
- UI truth: Score+Coverage, Rank+Denominator, Signal+Confidence
- Universe count != Scored count. Never show "Ready" when partially loaded.

### ROLE 7: RED TEAM ADVERSARY
- Attack: data delayed, API down, regime shift, Redis+API both fail
- Trust: Would PM trust? Would compliance approve?
- Run 3 Red Team scenarios after major changes.

